11
00:00:54,973 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:02,564
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,944
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,027 --> 00:01:11,281
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,364 --> 00:01:17,370
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:26,629 --> 00:01:29,591
OVERCAST

17
00:01:37,390 --> 00:01:39,559
<i>Regardless of how she came to
her conclusion,</i>

18
00:01:39,642 --> 00:01:42,020
<i>she knows the truth.</i>

19
00:01:42,979 --> 00:01:45,273
<i>If she gives this information
to the police...</i>

20
00:01:45,356 --> 00:01:49,319
<i>they'll figure out that
Light Yagami equals Kira.</i>

21
00:01:50,153 --> 00:01:51,446
<i>I have to finish her off.</i>

22
00:01:52,488 --> 00:01:53,489
What's wrong?

23
00:01:55,366 --> 00:01:56,534
Oh, nothing...

24
00:01:58,745 --> 00:02:01,873
I've been going over
what you just told me

25
00:02:02,457 --> 00:02:05,543
and I think that we should investigate
that theory as soon as possible.

26
00:02:06,419 --> 00:02:07,420
Really?

27
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:08,880
Yes.

28
00:02:09,005 --> 00:02:10,715
Have you told this to anyone else?

29
00:02:11,174 --> 00:02:13,217
No, you're the first.

30
00:02:15,261 --> 00:02:16,554
You're lucky.

31
00:02:16,679 --> 00:02:18,431
But how are you going to
eliminate her?

32
00:02:18,514 --> 00:02:20,642
Wouldn't it be bad
if you did it here?

33
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:24,145
<i>I've already figured that out...
without you telling me.</i>

34
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,981
Wow! So out in the open.

35
00:02:27,649 --> 00:02:31,027
Could you tell me the date
and time of the bus-jacking incident?

36
00:02:31,486 --> 00:02:34,489
It was on December 20,
in front of Asagao Hill.

37
00:02:34,906 --> 00:02:37,867
At 11:02.
Headed to Space Land.

38
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:44,415
December 20.
Headed to Space Land, right?

39
00:02:44,707 --> 00:02:45,750
Yes.

40
00:02:46,042 --> 00:02:49,504
SHOKO MAKI
SUICIDE JANUARY 1, 2007

41
00:02:49,587 --> 00:02:53,424
COMMITS SUICIDE IN A VVAY THAT NOBCDDY VVILL BE INCCDNVENIENCED AND HER BCDDY
VVILL NCDT BE DISCCDVERED. DIES BY IMPLEMENTING THIS PLAN VVITHIN 48 HCDLJRS.

42
00:02:55,426 --> 00:02:57,595
<i>Now no one will find her body.</i>

43
00:02:58,137 --> 00:02:59,555
<i>Even if they do find her,</i>

44
00:02:59,889 --> 00:03:02,558
<i>they'll assume that she killed herself
because of her fiance.</i>

45
00:03:05,770 --> 00:03:08,272
<i>Ryuk, what's so funny?</i>

46
00:03:14,153 --> 00:03:17,573
I'm very sorry for questioning
all of you individually.

47
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,451
Kira is not one of us.

48
00:03:22,787 --> 00:03:25,998
Ryuzaki, how can you definitely
say that he's not among us?

49
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:31,671
To be honest, I set some traps
to check if you were Kira, but...

50
00:03:32,422 --> 00:03:35,508
I didn't feel the need to
set them on any of you.

51
00:03:39,345 --> 00:03:40,346
Excuse me.

52
00:03:44,016 --> 00:03:46,936
<i>After he told us to
turn off our cell phones. . .!</i>

53
00:03:47,645 --> 00:03:48,646
I got it.

54
00:03:48,855 --> 00:03:50,314
I'm just about finished.

55
00:03:50,732 --> 00:03:52,400
Enter with your key.

56
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:55,862
Watari is on his way.

57
00:03:57,864 --> 00:03:58,865
I understand.

58
00:03:59,699 --> 00:04:02,618
If it's all right,
I'll report this incident.

59
00:04:02,869 --> 00:04:06,998
No, I'd like to report it myself.

60
00:04:07,248 --> 00:04:11,002
After talking to you, I've decided to
do it as soon as possible.

61
00:04:13,629 --> 00:04:14,672
I suppose you're right.

62
00:04:18,176 --> 00:04:20,470
<i>Just ten seconds until 1:15...</i>

63
00:04:21,888 --> 00:04:27,351
<i>I want to see how this woman dies,
but I can't be caught following her.</i>

64
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,774
<i>Go on. . hurry to your death!</i>

65
00:04:46,746 --> 00:04:48,706
Kira will definitely
be caught, won't he?

66
00:04:55,838 --> 00:04:58,508
<i>What's wrong? The time has passed...</i>

67
00:05:02,261 --> 00:05:03,304
<i>That's odd.</i>

68
00:05:03,805 --> 00:05:05,431
<i>Why isn't this woman leaving?</i>

69
00:05:06,516 --> 00:05:07,642
<i>My tests have proved that</i>

70
00:05:07,642 --> 00:05:13,314
SUICIDE

71
00:05:13,314 --> 00:05:14,732
<i>The criminals I tested all hanged
themselves at the times that I specified.</i>

72
00:05:15,483 --> 00:05:18,236
<i>I've proved many times that
I should be able</i>

73
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:20,154
<i>to control her within
these circumstances.</i>

74
00:05:21,531 --> 00:05:22,573
<i>So Why?</i>

75
00:05:28,663 --> 00:05:29,705
<i>Ryuk...</i>

76
00:05:30,206 --> 00:05:31,290
<i>Come to think of it,</i>

77
00:05:31,374 --> 00:05:33,918
<i>he was laughing oddly when
I was writing in the Death Note...</i>

78
00:05:34,544 --> 00:05:35,753
<i>That's not all.</i>

79
00:05:36,087 --> 00:05:39,131
<i>The way he laughed when I asked
for her name was also bizarre...</i>

80
00:05:40,049 --> 00:05:42,385
<i>Both were times when something had
to do with her name...</i>

81
00:05:43,636 --> 00:05:44,637
<i>An alias!</i>

82
00:05:54,564 --> 00:05:56,566
Thank you all for working so hard.

83
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:59,610
T-This person is Watari?

84
00:05:59,944 --> 00:06:01,779
Um, where are your usual clothes?

85
00:06:02,572 --> 00:06:04,365
If I had dressed like I usually do,

86
00:06:04,448 --> 00:06:06,117
it would be like telling everyone
I'm Watari.

87
00:06:06,409 --> 00:06:09,704
It would also give away Ryuzaki's
location in this hotel.

88
00:06:10,246 --> 00:06:11,664
L-| see.

89
00:06:12,248 --> 00:06:18,296
Showing my face in front of you
all means you've won Ryuzaki's trust.

90
00:06:18,462 --> 00:06:20,882
L-| feel kind of honored...

91
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:27,179
Ryuzaki, I've brought what
you've requested.

92
00:06:27,763 --> 00:06:29,515
Please pass them out to everyone.

93
00:06:29,807 --> 00:06:30,808
Yes.

94
00:06:33,978 --> 00:06:36,355
These are everyone's new police IDs.

95
00:06:36,856 --> 00:06:37,982
New?

96
00:06:40,693 --> 00:06:42,820
<i>An alias.
That's the only thing it could be!</i>

97
00:06:43,613 --> 00:06:46,824
<i>Ryuk can see her real name.</i>

98
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:49,035
<i>That's why he was laughing.</i>

99
00:06:49,827 --> 00:06:52,830
<i>This woman was being careful
from the start.</i>

100
00:06:53,623 --> 00:06:54,665
<i>That's right.</i>

101
00:06:54,749 --> 00:06:58,753
<i>She believes that Raye died...
because he showed his ID.</i>

102
00:06:59,754 --> 00:07:02,715
<i>That's why she's acting without
revealing her identity.</i>

103
00:07:03,466 --> 00:07:04,508
<i>This isn't good.</i>

104
00:07:05,134 --> 00:07:07,094
<i>It's even harder to ask
for the real name</i>

105
00:07:07,178 --> 00:07:09,472
<i>of someone who has already
given an alias.</i>

106
00:07:10,014 --> 00:07:12,600
<i>If I keep asking her persistently,
she'll get suspicious.</i>

107
00:07:13,184 --> 00:07:16,687
<i>More importantly, it's suspicious
that I knew she was using an alias.</i>

108
00:07:18,773 --> 00:07:20,483
I should be getting back soon.

109
00:07:22,068 --> 00:07:24,236
Someone might have come back.

110
00:07:24,820 --> 00:07:27,198
Oh, yeah.
I suppose you're right.

111
00:07:27,657 --> 00:07:29,408
Hopefully, someone did.

112
00:07:30,076 --> 00:07:31,077
Yes.

113
00:07:34,497 --> 00:07:35,581
<i>Damn it. . .!</i>

114
00:07:35,998 --> 00:07:37,875
<i>It would also be unnatural
to try to turn her back.</i>

115
00:07:42,171 --> 00:07:44,757
<i>What should I do? At this rate...</i>

116
00:07:45,591 --> 00:07:46,842
<i>Oh no...</i>

117
00:07:47,426 --> 00:07:49,220
<i>If my father calls...</i>

118
00:07:49,470 --> 00:07:51,806
<i>I promised her that I'd let her
talk to him!</i>

119
00:07:52,473 --> 00:07:54,183
<i>It's all over if he calls!</i>

120
00:07:54,684 --> 00:07:55,726
<i>What do I do?</i>

121
00:07:56,519 --> 00:08:02,108
<i>What am I thinking about?
I can just turn off my cell phone.</i>

122
00:08:04,318 --> 00:08:05,319
<i>Calm down.</i>

123
00:08:05,861 --> 00:08:08,406
<i>I just have to find out her name.</i>

124
00:08:08,698 --> 00:08:12,576
<i>Her purse, her pocket,
she's got to have a driver's license...</i>

125
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:14,954
<i>or some sort of personal ID
on her somewhere.</i>

126
00:08:15,246 --> 00:08:16,580
<i>She's a woman.</i>

127
00:08:16,872 --> 00:08:18,541
<i>If it comes down to it,
I can use force...</i>

128
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:20,710
<i>That's stupid!</i>

129
00:08:20,793 --> 00:08:23,045
<i>I can '1' do anything that 'll
cause a stir here- - .</i>

130
00:08:23,379 --> 00:08:25,297
<i>I've got to get her to
somewhere isolated.</i>

131
00:08:25,673 --> 00:08:28,426
<i>Where? What explanation
can I offer...</i>

132
00:08:28,884 --> 00:08:31,429
<i>...this extremely cautious woman?</i>

133
00:08:31,679 --> 00:08:34,015
<i>No, I've got to change
my plan of attack...</i>

134
00:08:34,223 --> 00:08:35,349
<i>I can do this.</i>

135
00:08:35,558 --> 00:08:37,727
<i>I can get her name without
setting any alarms off.</i>

136
00:08:40,438 --> 00:08:41,605
Light.

137
00:08:41,689 --> 00:08:44,442
We can do that eye deal anytime...

138
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:47,069
It's no different from putting
on contact lenses.

139
00:08:47,486 --> 00:08:48,696
It takes just a few seconds.

140
00:08:49,155 --> 00:08:53,534
<i>I won't have my remaining life
halved by the likes of this woman.</i>

141
00:08:54,243 --> 00:08:57,496
<i>No, I won't ever consider the deal!</i>

142
00:08:57,955 --> 00:08:58,956
<i>Don't bother me.</i>

143
00:08:59,415 --> 00:09:00,624
<i>Shut up, Shinigami!</i>

144
00:09:02,251 --> 00:09:03,335
Excuse me.

145
00:09:03,419 --> 00:09:04,462
Yes?

146
00:09:04,837 --> 00:09:07,214
Do you still have business
at the police department?

147
00:09:08,007 --> 00:09:09,884
I'll be all right by myself.

148
00:09:12,178 --> 00:09:13,220
I understand.

149
00:09:14,388 --> 00:09:16,432
Our names and ranks are all fake.

150
00:09:17,016 --> 00:09:18,893
Fake police IDs?!

151
00:09:19,477 --> 00:09:22,521
Kira requires a name
and a face to kill.

152
00:09:24,231 --> 00:09:26,275
We are challenging Kira
with that premise in mind.

153
00:09:26,692 --> 00:09:28,027
This is only natural.

154
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:31,614
B-But a police officer
with a fake ID is...

155
00:09:31,697 --> 00:09:35,159
No, if Kira needs a name to kill,

156
00:09:35,659 --> 00:09:39,497
an alias would go a long way
in protecting our lives.

157
00:09:39,997 --> 00:09:41,499
We should carry these around.

158
00:09:41,957 --> 00:09:43,417
I think so, too.

159
00:09:43,542 --> 00:09:44,585
Yeah.

160
00:09:44,794 --> 00:09:48,380
When you have to give out
your name to strangers,

161
00:09:48,714 --> 00:09:51,217
use the alias in your IDs.

162
00:09:51,634 --> 00:09:52,676
Yes.

163
00:09:53,344 --> 00:09:56,388
Please be careful not to use them

164
00:09:56,472 --> 00:09:57,890
inside the police headquarters.

165
00:09:58,349 --> 00:10:00,184
It could cause problems.

166
00:10:00,893 --> 00:10:02,144
Understood.

167
00:10:02,478 --> 00:10:07,525
Well then...
I want everyone to wear these belts.

168
00:10:07,775 --> 00:10:08,818
Belts?

169
00:10:09,902 --> 00:10:12,363
There is a tracking device
in the buckle.

170
00:10:12,822 --> 00:10:15,699
This way, Ryuzaki will know
your whereabouts.

171
00:10:16,075 --> 00:10:18,119
And when you press
the buckle twice...

172
00:10:20,329 --> 00:10:22,206
My cell phone will ring.

173
00:10:23,374 --> 00:10:26,710
And I'll call you back immediately.

174
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:30,673
In the morning, you will go to work
at the police department.

175
00:10:30,756 --> 00:10:32,716
Later, using this method...

176
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,345
I shall confirm our hotel
and room number.

177
00:10:36,929 --> 00:10:39,140
Please use this
for emergencies as well.

178
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:41,058
This is kind of cool.

179
00:10:41,142 --> 00:10:43,644
It's like we're a special force
chasing Kira!

180
00:10:43,936 --> 00:10:44,979
Matsuda!

181
00:10:45,062 --> 00:10:46,564
This isn't child's play.

182
00:10:47,022 --> 00:10:48,315
Don't joke around.

183
00:10:48,941 --> 00:10:49,942
Okay. . -

184
00:10:50,234 --> 00:10:52,444
Thank you very much.

185
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:56,532
Thanks to you, I have gained
confidence in my theory.

186
00:10:57,074 --> 00:10:58,075
Not at all...

187
00:11:04,832 --> 00:11:07,418
<i>Since Ryuk brought up the eye deal...</i>

188
00:11:07,918 --> 00:11:10,337
<i>There's no doubt.
She's using an alias.</i>

189
00:11:11,463 --> 00:11:15,801
<i>At this rate, with her theory that
Kira was on the bus...</i>

190
00:11:16,343 --> 00:11:18,596
<i>and given the people Raye Penber
was tasked to investigate,</i>

191
00:11:18,762 --> 00:11:20,848
<i>the police will immediately suspect me.</i>

192
00:11:22,975 --> 00:11:25,853
Hey, she's leaving.
Is that okay?

193
00:11:27,188 --> 00:11:30,107
<i>It should be about five minutes until
she reaches the police headquarters...</i>

194
00:11:30,566 --> 00:11:31,734
<i>Think...</i>

195
00:11:32,193 --> 00:11:35,112
<i>How can I get her name
within five minutes?</i>

196
00:11:48,584 --> 00:11:50,294
<i>She's going to
the police headquarters.</i>

197
00:11:50,753 --> 00:11:54,632
<i>If someone from the task force
has returned, I'm finished.</i>

198
00:11:55,424 --> 00:11:58,886
<i>Somehow, I've got to find out
her real name and eliminate her...</i>

199
00:11:59,595 --> 00:12:02,306
<i>Now there are only three minutes until
she reaches the police headquarters.</i>

200
00:12:03,599 --> 00:12:04,642
<i>All right.</i>

201
00:12:06,352 --> 00:12:07,645
What are you going to do?

202
00:12:07,853 --> 00:12:08,896
Excuse me.

203
00:12:08,938 --> 00:12:09,980
Yes?

204
00:12:10,272 --> 00:12:13,150
There's something I haven't told you.

205
00:12:13,359 --> 00:12:14,318
Okay. . -

206
00:12:15,444 --> 00:12:19,490
It's impossible to contact anyone
directly in headquarters.

207
00:12:21,408 --> 00:12:23,118
<i>I have to conduct this conversation
naturally and</i>

208
00:12:23,202 --> 00:12:26,163
<i>connect it to something
that she'll latch onto.</i>

209
00:12:26,622 --> 00:12:28,666
<i>Within that time,
I'll draw out her name.</i>

210
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:30,584
<i>I can do this.</i>

211
00:12:31,252 --> 00:12:32,836
What do you mean?

212
00:12:33,128 --> 00:12:35,965
Don't you think that it's odd
that there's no one at headquarters?

213
00:12:36,257 --> 00:12:37,508
Y-Yes.

214
00:12:37,758 --> 00:12:39,593
I thought it was strange, but...

215
00:12:40,052 --> 00:12:45,849
The team investigating Kira is structured
so no one knows who is involved.

216
00:12:47,935 --> 00:12:52,189
If the general public knows how
the team is structured,

217
00:12:52,481 --> 00:12:56,193
a tragedy like the one involving
your fiancé may happen again...

218
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:02,783
I understand.

219
00:13:03,325 --> 00:13:06,870
That's why you were told
that no one was at the headquarters.

220
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:09,540
In other words,

221
00:13:09,832 --> 00:13:14,044
you will never be allowed to talk
directly to someone from headquarters.

222
00:13:16,463 --> 00:13:19,883
<i>That's good, Light.</i>

223
00:13:20,592 --> 00:13:23,637
Why do you know so much?

224
00:13:24,596 --> 00:13:26,890
She's pretty sharp.

225
00:13:30,311 --> 00:13:32,479
I guess I have no choice.
I shall tell you...

226
00:13:33,689 --> 00:13:36,191
It's because I'm a member of
the task force.

227
00:13:37,526 --> 00:13:39,737
You're part of the task force?

228
00:13:40,112 --> 00:13:41,155
Yes.

229
00:13:41,363 --> 00:13:44,366
I is currently in charge
of the task force.

230
00:13:44,825 --> 00:13:47,202
Yes, I thought so.

231
00:13:48,203 --> 00:13:51,415
I was troubled because there weren't
enough detectives at headquarters.

232
00:13:51,874 --> 00:13:54,668
Many quit because
they're afraid of Kira.

233
00:13:55,377 --> 00:13:57,421
I'm just a high school student, but...

234
00:13:57,713 --> 00:14:02,259
I've helped the police
solve two cases in the past.

235
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:05,054
So he was convinced by that...?

236
00:14:05,387 --> 00:14:07,931
I can enter the headquarters
whenever I wish,

237
00:14:08,223 --> 00:14:10,934
and I'm allowed to investigate
on my own.

238
00:14:11,643 --> 00:14:15,272
In other words, the people who
are currently at task force headquarters...

239
00:14:15,356 --> 00:14:18,609
are the chosen few who...

240
00:14:18,734 --> 00:14:22,404
are trusted and highly qualified

241
00:14:34,917 --> 00:14:35,918
I understand.

242
00:14:36,251 --> 00:14:39,963
But just in case,
I think I'll visit the headquarters.

243
00:14:40,589 --> 00:14:41,799
Thank you very much.

244
00:14:44,593 --> 00:14:46,136
Please wait!

245
00:14:47,262 --> 00:14:50,099
I just told you that
you can't talk to anyone.

246
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:53,310
I would like to talk directly to L.

247
00:14:58,273 --> 00:15:01,485
Come to think of it,
who's at headquarters now?

248
00:15:01,902 --> 00:15:03,612
Right now, no one.

249
00:15:04,113 --> 00:15:05,155
That's not good.

250
00:15:05,697 --> 00:15:08,492
Have at least one person
there at all times.

251
00:15:08,784 --> 00:15:09,827
Understood.

252
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:11,995
Aizawa, if you could
stay there for today...

253
00:15:12,204 --> 00:15:14,998
Okay. I can get there
quickly from here.

254
00:15:15,624 --> 00:15:17,501
Ms. Maki, please wait.

255
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,586
It's impossible to meet L.

256
00:15:20,087 --> 00:15:21,171
It's useless.

257
00:15:25,926 --> 00:15:29,138
He might...allow me to meet him.

258
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:30,013
What?

259
00:15:30,139 --> 00:15:33,308
I only followed his orders from
beyond a computer screen, but...

260
00:15:33,809 --> 00:15:39,440
Two years ago in America
I worked on a case under L.

261
00:15:40,482 --> 00:15:42,192
You worked under L?

262
00:15:43,318 --> 00:15:47,865
Until three months ago,
I was an FBI agent.

263
00:15:49,658 --> 00:15:52,202
<i>This is it...
I can use this.</i>

264
00:15:53,328 --> 00:15:54,705
Is that so?

265
00:15:55,164 --> 00:15:59,710
It's no wonder. Your actions are
not amateurish.

266
00:16:00,169 --> 00:16:03,547
You move carefully and wisely
as you get to the heart of the matter.

267
00:16:04,339 --> 00:16:05,841
I'd like to learn from you.

268
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:10,220
It's amazing how you can
line up all those lies like that.

269
00:16:11,096 --> 00:16:13,474
I must approach this case
in my own way.

270
00:16:13,515 --> 00:16:18,061
I have to suspect the police
and even the people within task force.

271
00:16:18,937 --> 00:16:20,981
But I trust L.

272
00:16:23,025 --> 00:16:24,735
I thought that
if I went to headquarters

273
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:30,741
and have them verify my name and face...
I'd be able to speak directly to L.

274
00:16:31,283 --> 00:16:32,534
I see...

275
00:16:33,035 --> 00:16:36,580
But why did you tell me that
you wanted to talk to L?

276
00:16:37,789 --> 00:16:39,917
When I wasn't allowed to see
someone from the task force,

277
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,878
I was angry and then
I ran into someone

278
00:16:42,961 --> 00:16:45,255
who claimed to be
the son of the lead detective...

279
00:16:46,048 --> 00:16:47,925
No, that's not it.

280
00:16:49,468 --> 00:16:50,928
I'll tell you the truth.

281
00:16:51,553 --> 00:16:53,597
You seemed like L.

282
00:16:55,557 --> 00:16:57,267
I felt that you two are similar.

283
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,403
Shall we investigate
the case together?

284
00:17:08,737 --> 00:17:09,404
Huh?

285
00:17:10,239 --> 00:17:13,450
Will you work as
a member in the task force?

286
00:17:14,826 --> 00:17:17,079
Of course,
not just anybody is allowed.

287
00:17:17,913 --> 00:17:20,707
But we need people like you!

288
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:24,753
You could be doing more than
gathering general information.

289
00:17:25,254 --> 00:17:27,589
You were an FBI agent.

290
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:30,759
You're more talented than
our current detectives.

291
00:17:31,552 --> 00:17:33,303
Even L trusted you.

292
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:37,641
To join the task force,
you need proper identification,

293
00:17:38,016 --> 00:17:40,435
a recommendation from
a current detective on the team,

294
00:17:40,519 --> 00:17:42,729
and finally L's permission.

295
00:17:43,105 --> 00:17:44,982
You want me to join
the task force?

296
00:17:45,774 --> 00:17:48,652
It's fate that we met here!

297
00:17:49,611 --> 00:17:51,321
I'll recommend you!

298
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:56,994
Oh, sorry.

299
00:17:57,703 --> 00:17:58,996
I just got a little excited...

300
00:17:59,454 --> 00:18:00,581
N-No, it's okay...

301
00:18:00,956 --> 00:18:04,668
Even if you can cooperate
with the investigation,

302
00:18:05,294 --> 00:18:07,087
I understand you have personal
circumstances to attend to.

303
00:18:07,296 --> 00:18:09,506
Especially since you live in America...

304
00:18:10,632 --> 00:18:13,343
I was planning to continue living
with my fiancé in America,

305
00:18:13,468 --> 00:18:15,596
he and I were to be
married this spring.

306
00:18:15,804 --> 00:18:17,848
But now that he's dead...

307
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:21,351
I have no idea what I'll do now...

308
00:18:21,476 --> 00:18:22,519
<i>All right...</i>

309
00:18:22,603 --> 00:18:25,147
<i>I've come this far,
I just have to push a little bit...</i>

310
00:18:25,939 --> 00:18:28,358
But you're still very young
and beautiful.

311
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:30,611
You shouldn't be involved
in such a dangerous investigation...

312
00:18:30,736 --> 00:18:33,864
No! I don't have anything to lose.

313
00:18:33,989 --> 00:18:35,324
I want to catch Kira!

314
00:18:35,574 --> 00:18:37,826
It's all I want to do!

315
00:18:38,118 --> 00:18:39,995
Please let me investigate with you!

316
00:18:49,421 --> 00:18:50,464
Thank goodness.

317
00:18:51,256 --> 00:18:54,301
Well, may I see something that may act
as some form of personal ID?

318
00:18:55,344 --> 00:18:56,386
Well...

319
00:18:56,637 --> 00:18:57,638
Yes?

320
00:18:57,763 --> 00:19:02,351
Actually, that name I gave you earlier
was not my real name...

321
00:19:02,934 --> 00:19:03,894
I'm very sorry.

322
00:19:06,188 --> 00:19:07,481
That's all right.

323
00:19:07,856 --> 00:19:11,193
Amazing! Who would have thought
you were being so careful?

324
00:19:11,693 --> 00:19:13,320
You're one step ahead of me.

325
00:19:13,654 --> 00:19:16,573
That's even further proof
that you're qualified.

326
00:19:16,823 --> 00:19:19,076
Is a Japanese driver's license okay?

327
00:19:19,451 --> 00:19:20,410
Yes.

328
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,764
<i>I made it...</i>

329
00:19:41,306 --> 00:19:43,350
NAOMI MISORA DOB 2/11/1979

330
00:19:43,392 --> 00:19:44,935
NAOMI MISORA SUICIDE 1/1/2007 COMMITS SUICIDE IN A VVAY THAT NOBODY VVILL BE INCONVENIENCED
AND HER BODY VVILL NOT BE DISCOVERED. DIES BY IMPLEMENTING THIS PLAN VVITHIN 48 HOURS.

331
00:19:57,489 --> 00:20:01,284
Excuse me, but why do you
keep looking at your watch?

332
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:03,620
Oh. . .this?

333
00:20:05,330 --> 00:20:06,373
It's because...

334
00:20:09,918 --> 00:20:11,044
I'm Kira.

335
00:20:41,950 --> 00:20:42,951
What's the matter?

336
00:20:44,453 --> 00:20:46,246
There's something I have to do.

337
00:20:47,247 --> 00:20:48,248
Oh.

338
00:20:50,292 --> 00:20:52,669
My father's cell phone is on now.

339
00:20:53,628 --> 00:20:55,130
Don't you want to talk to him?

340
00:20:56,381 --> 00:20:58,675
I have nothing I want to talk about.

341
00:21:00,635 --> 00:21:03,346
Good bye, Miss Naomi Misora.

342
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:25,869
TO BE CONTINUED

343
00:21:27,287 --> 00:21:32,209
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

344
00:21:32,334 --> 00:21:37,672
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

345
00:21:37,839 --> 00:21:46,681
<i>I'm holding these feelings
that I can't give up in my heart</i>

346
00:21:46,765 --> 00:21:53,021
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

347
00:21:53,104 --> 00:21:57,651
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

348
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:03,240
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

349
00:22:03,532 --> 00:22:07,077
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

350
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:10,747
<i>To accomplish</i>

351
00:22:11,373 --> 00:22:15,919
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

352
00:22:16,044 --> 00:22:21,716
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

353
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:26,763
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

354
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:32,561
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

355
00:22:36,773 --> 00:22:38,775
PREVIEW

356
00:22:38,775 --> 00:22:40,235
With Ryuk's information
and my prior preparations,

357
00:22:40,277 --> 00:22:43,488
I can kill criminals
currently being broadcast...

358
00:22:43,613 --> 00:22:48,410
while masquerading as
a regular high school student.

359
00:22:49,244 --> 00:22:51,037
Just watch, L!

360
00:22:51,037 --> 00:22:51,788
NEXT EPISODE: GLARE

